Problem 1: A Detailed View to MNIST Classification¶

1.1 Training a fully-connected net for MNIST classification¶

In [2]:
mnist = tf.keras.datasets.mnist
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
x_train.shape
y_train.shape
x_test.shape
y_test.shape
Out[2]:
(60000, 28, 28)
Out[2]:
(60000,)
Out[2]:
(10000, 28, 28)
Out[2]:
(10000,)
In [3]:
# reshaping the data

x_train = x_train.reshape(60000, 784)
x_test = x_test.reshape(10000, 784)
In [4]:
# Normalizing the data

x_train, x_test = x_train / 255.0, x_test / 255.0
In [5]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

model = Sequential()
model.add(Dense(1024, input_dim = 784))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dense(1024))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dense(1024))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dense(1024))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dense(1024))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(Dense(10))
model.add(Activation('softmax'))

model.summary()

# Calculating loss and optimizing it

loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss=loss_fn,
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Fitting the model

In [11]:
# Creating a list to store maximum probability and its index 

prob_mat = []
for j in range(softmax_preds.shape[0]):
  prob_mat.append([j,max(softmax_preds[j]),np.argmax(softmax_preds[j])])
prob_mat = np.array(prob_mat)
In [12]:
# plotting the top probablities value of each label

fig, ax = plt.subplots(10,10,figsize=(30,30))
for i in range(10):
  prob_mat1 = prob_mat[prob_mat[:,2] == i]
  prob_mat1 = prob_mat1[prob_mat1[:,1].argsort()][::-1]
  prob_mat1 = prob_mat1[0:10] 
  for j in range(prob_mat1.shape[0]):
    ax[i][j].imshow(x_test1000[int(prob_mat1[j][0])].reshape(28,28))

By randomly selecting 10 dimensions out of 1024 dimensions, we can see that they are able to capture the features of some of the digits. Some images are blank because these dimensions are not capturing any information about other digits. The ideal situation would be when data can be seperated based on its label.

1.5 tSNE and PCA¶

In [101]:
cols = ['pixel'+str(i) for i in range(x_test1000.shape[1])]
df_test = pd.DataFrame(x_test1000,columns=cols)
df_test['y'] = y_test1000
df_test['label'] = df_test['y'].apply(lambda i: str(i))
In [20]:
# PCA

pca = PCA(n_components=2)
pca_result = pca.fit_transform(df_test[cols].values)
df_test['pca1'] = pca_result[:,0]
df_test['pca2'] = pca_result[:,1] 

print('Explained variation per principal component: {}'.format(pca.explained_variance_ratio_))

pca_mean = df_test.groupby('label').agg({'pca1':'mean', 'pca2':'mean'})
pca_mean.reset_index(inplace = True)
pca1_mean = pca_mean['pca1'].values
pca2_mean = pca_mean['pca2'].values

plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
sns.scatterplot(x="pca1", y="pca2", hue = 'y', palette=sns.color_palette("hls", 10), data=df_test, legend="full", edgecolor='None')
for i in range(0,10):
  plt.annotate(i, (pca1_mean[i], pca2_mean[i]),size=18)
plt.xlabel("PCA1")
plt.ylabel("PCA2")
plt.title("PCA")

Problem 2: Adult Optimization¶

In [37]:
mnist = tf.keras.datasets.mnist
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
In [38]:
# Normalizing the data

x_train, x_test = x_train / 255.0, x_test / 255.0

SGD optimizer¶

a) Activation function: the logistic sigmoid function; initialization: random numbers generated from the normal distribution (µ = 0, σ = 0.01)¶

In [39]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01))])

model.summary()

In [40]:
# Calculating loss and optimizing it

loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.SGD(learning_rate=0.01),
              loss=loss_fn,
              metrics=['accuracy'])
In [41]:
# Fitting the model

model.fit(x_train, y_train, validation_data=(x_test,y_test), epochs=350, callbacks=[hist], batch_size=150)

In [43]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal())])

model.summary()

# Calculating loss and optimizing it

loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.SGD(learning_rate=0.01),
              loss=loss_fn,
              metrics=['accuracy'])

# Fitting the model

model.fit(x_train, y_train, validation_data=(x_test,y_test), epochs=350, callbacks=[hist], batch_size=150)

In [47]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer(mean=0.0, stddev=0.01))])

model.summary()

In [51]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal())])

model.summary()

# Calculating loss and optimizing it

loss_fn = tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True)

              loss=loss_fn,
              metrics=['accuracy'])

e) Activation function: ReLU; initialization: Kaiming He’s initializer¶

In [55]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal())])

model.summary()

Plotting the learning curve¶

In [59]:
df_sgd_acc = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(sgd_acc1, sgd_acc2, sgd_acc3, sgd_acc4, sgd_acc5)),
               columns =['sig_rand_acc', 'sig_xavier_acc', 'relu_rand_acc', 'relu_xavier_acc', 'relu_kaiming_acc'])
df_sgd_acc['epochs'] = [i for i in range(1,351)]

plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
plt.plot(df_sgd_acc['sig_rand_acc'],label='Logistic Sigmoid with Normal Distribution')
plt.plot(df_sgd_acc['sig_xavier_acc'],label='Logistic Sigmoid with Xavier')
plt.plot(df_sgd_acc['relu_rand_acc'],label='Relu with Normal Distribution')
plt.plot(df_sgd_acc['relu_xavier_acc'],label='Relu with Xavier')
plt.plot(df_sgd_acc['relu_kaiming_acc'],label='Relu with Kaiming He')
plt.xlabel('Epochs')
plt.ylabel('Test Accuracy')
plt.title('SGD Optimizer')
plt.legend()

Adam optimizer¶

a) Activation function: the logistic sigmoid function; initialization: random numbers generated from the normal distribution (µ = 0, σ = 0.01)¶

In [60]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01))])

model.summary()

In [83]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal())])

model.summary()

b) Activation function: the logistic sigmoid function; initialization: Xavier initializer; with dropout rate: 0.2 for the first layer and 0.5 for the other hidden layers¶

In [87]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='sigmoid', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.GlorotNormal())])

model.summary()

In [92]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal())])

model.summary()

d) Activation function: ReLU; initialization: Kaiming He’s initializer; with dropout rate: 0.2 for the first layer and 0.5 for the other hidden layers¶

In [96]:
# Building a model and adding 5 hidden layers with 1024 hidden units and output layer with 10 units

hist = History()

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
  tf.keras.layers.Flatten(input_shape = (28,28)),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl1'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.2, noise_shape=None),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl2'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5, noise_shape=None),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl3'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5, noise_shape=None),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name='hl4'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5, noise_shape=None),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(1024, activation='relu', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal(), name= 'hl5'),
  tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5, noise_shape=None),
  tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', kernel_initializer=tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal())])

model.summary()

               columns =['no_dropout_train_loss', 'no_dropout_test_loss', 'dropout_train_loss', 'dropout_test_loss'])

plt.plot(df_relu_loss['epochs'], df_relu_loss['no_dropout_train_loss'], label = "No Dropout: Train Loss")

plt.legend()
plt.show()
